      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 2.24,
      "endTime": 9.07
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_3",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "What false impression does an ocean wave convey to the observer?",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 9.08,
      "endTime": 15.36,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "What",
            "label": "疑问词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "What",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "什么"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "intro_4",
      "role": "Narrator",
      "text": "Waves are the children of the struggle between ocean and atmosphere, the ongoing signatures of infinity.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 15.37,
      "endTime": 23.25,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "are",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s1",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Rays from the sun excite and energize the atmosphere of the earth, awakening it to flow, to movement, to rhythm, to life.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 23.26,
      "endTime": 33.28,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s2",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The wind then speaks the message of the sun to the sea",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 33.29,
      "endTime": 37.19
    },
    {
      "id": "s3",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "and the sea transmits it on through waves--an ancient, exquisite powerful message.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 37.2,
      "endTime": 45.47,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s4",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "These ocean waves are among the earth's most complicated natural phenomena.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 45.48,
      "endTime": 51.44,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "are",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s5",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "The basic features include a crest (the highest point of the wave),",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 51.45,
      "endTime": 56.12
    },
    {
      "id": "s6",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "a trough (the lowest point), a height (the vertical distance from the trough to the crest),",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 56.13,
      "endTime": 63.66
    },
    {
      "id": "s7",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "a wave length (the horizontal distance between two wave crests),",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 63.67,
      "endTime": 68.98
    },
    {
      "id": "s8",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "and a period (which is the time it takes awave crest to travel one wave length).",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 68.99,
      "endTime": 76.2,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          },
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s9",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "Although an ocean wave gives the impression of a wall of water moving in your direction,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 76.21,
      "endTime": 82.45,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "your",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Your",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "你的，你们的"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s10",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "in actuality waves move through the water leaving the water about where it was.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 82.46,
      "endTime": 89.35,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s11",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "If the water was moving with the wave,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 89.36,
      "endTime": 92.05
    },
    {
      "id": "s12",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "the ocean and everything on it would be racing in to the shore with obviously catastrophic results.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 92.06,
      "endTime": 100.02,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s13",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "An ocean wave passing through deep water causes a particle on the surface to move in a roughly circular orbit,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 100.03,
      "endTime": 108.48
    },
    {
      "id": "s14",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "drawing the particle first towards the advancing wave, then up into the wave,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 108.49,
      "endTime": 114.4
    },
    {
      "id": "s15",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "then forward with it and then--as the wave leaves the particles behind--back to its starting point again.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 114.41,
      "endTime": 123.29,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          },
          {
            "text": "its",
            "label": "形容词性物主代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s16",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "From both maturity to death, a wave is subject to the same laws as any other 'living' thing.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 123.3,
      "endTime": 130.14,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s17",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "For a time it assumes a miraculous individuality that, in the end, is reabsorbed into the great ocean of life.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 130.15,
      "endTime": 139.1,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "it",
            "label": "人称代词/主语"
          },
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          },
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "It",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "它"
          },
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          },
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s18",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "The undulating waves of the open sea are generated by three natural causes:",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 139.11,
      "endTime": 145.24,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "are",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          }
        ],
        "words": []
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s19",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "wind, earth movements or tremors, and the gravitational pull of the moon and the sun.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 145.25,
      "endTime": 151.94
    },
    {
      "id": "s20",
      "role": "Woman",
      "text": "Once waves have been generated,",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 151.95,
      "endTime": 154.13
    },
    {
      "id": "s21",
      "role": "Man",
      "text": "gravity is the force that drives them in a continual attempt to restore the ocean surface to a flat plain.",
      "translation": "",
      "startTime": 154.14,
      "endTime": 159.14,
      "analysis": {
        "grammar": [
          {
            "text": "is",
            "label": "谓语/系动词"
          },
          {
            "text": "that",
            "label": "指示代词"
          }
        ],
        "words": [
          {
            "word": "Is",
            "pos": "v.",
            "meaning": "是"
          },
          {
            "word": "That",
            "pos": "pron.",
            "meaning": "那个"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}